(99, 1, '2018-09-13 13:21:35', '2018-09-13 13:21:35', '<strong>Works as advertised. Nothing less, nothing more. Begginers: Yes; Professionals: No</strong>\r\n\r\nI purchased this keyboard as an absolute beginner to learn to play on as an adult. Knowing I would have limited time to practice I was looking for an affordable option that would not break the bank. After reading other reviews this seemed to be a viable option so I pulled the trigger. So keep in mind that my review comes from the position of an absolute beginner and here are my thoughts...\r\n\r\nThis keyboard is a good option for a beginner to learn on before moving on to a more expensive option if you decide you do enjoy the hobby. The keyboard works exactly as advertised. Nothing more, nothing less. I do feel like anyone with experience playing on a nicer or professional keyboard would not enjoy playing on this one as the keys have a \"toy like\" feel and spring to them. But overall everything works as it should. I\'m not overly blown away, but it gets the job done. I feel certain this will be all the keyboard I need to learn how to properly play music. With that said I will finish off with some pro\'s and con\'s.\r\n\r\n<strong>Pro\'s:</strong>\r\n-Comes with a fairly sturdy stand, nice seat, decent head phones and mic (have not used the mic)\r\n-Lots of different options as far as instruments and backup beats to choose from\r\n-Decent sounding speakers if you choose not to use the headphones\r\n-Keys are easy to play and move freely\r\n-Good beginner setup to learn on\r\n-works as advertised\r\n-items were well packaged\r\n\r\n<strong>Con\'s:</strong>\r\n-My biggest Con - DOES NOT COME WITH A 10v POWER ADAPTER. There IS a place to plug in a power adapter on the back of the keyboard yet it did NOT come with one in the box. I had to find one from another appliance I had around the house. Yes, you can use this keyboard with batteries but it did not come with those either. I feel like most people would rather plug it in then use batteries. My opinion would have been to leave the mic out and include a power adapter. I think more people would use the adapter then the mic.\r\n-keys seem very toy like. They have a spring like feel to them and are a little noisy\r\n-the music sheet holder sits in the rail very loosely so if you bump it at all it will fall off. Anything heavy falls off.\r\n-when the instrument is set to standard piano, low keys sound fine but the high keys sound a little off, a little digital (no pun intended)\r\n-the on/off button is like something off of an early 1980s toy. It is not a huge deal but it does seem like the one thing that is out of place\r\n\r\nIf they would have included a power adapter and the keys had just slightly better feel, I would have given 5 stars. In the end though I would recommend this for a beginner.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/Hamzer-Portable-Electronic-Headphones-Microphone/dp/B0714JFQ7F/ref=sr_1_4?s=musical-instruments&amp;ie=UTF8&amp;qid=1536844482&amp;sr=1-4&amp;keywords=pianos#customerReviews\"><strong>Buy Here</strong></a>', 'Hamzer 61-Key Portable Electronic Keyboard Piano with Stand, Stool, Headphones & Microphone', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'hamzer-portable-electronic-keyboard-piano', '', '', '2018-09-13 13:21:35', '2018-09-13 13:21:35', '', 0, 'http://musicreview/?p=99', 0, 'post', '', 0),
